LIM DOO, alias Lim Ock Gong, Appellant, v. John D. NAGLE, as Commissioner of Immigration for the Port of San Francisco, California, Appellee. No. 6793. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 20, 1932. Stephen M. White, of San Francisco, Cal._ for appellant. Geo. J. Hatfield, U. S. Atty., and Arthur Phelan, U. S. Immigration Service, both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and NETERER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of appellant, ordered appeal dismissed.
